{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`src/render.ts` owns fake cursor rendering for visual render paths and `restyleCursorMarker()` for Pi-rendered prompt output. `renderCursorCell()` currently renders `bar` as a styled `\u258c` glyph, which replaces the cursor cell instead of styling the real cell. This preserves render width, but it hides the character under the cursor. The extension already sends DECSCUSR cursor-shape hints through `cursorShapeEscape(\"bar\")`, so the actual terminal cursor can remain a vertical bar while the rendered "}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Render `bar` cursor cells without removing or hiding the underlying character."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 23", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Render `bar` by styling the existing cell, not replacing it Change `renderCursorCell(cell, \"bar\")` to wrap `safeCell` in the bar cursor style instead of returning the `BAR_CURSOR_GLYPH`. For empty/end-of-line cursor cells, continue rendering a styled space."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_render_bar_by_styling_the_existing_cell_not_replacing_it", "label": "Render bar by styling the existing cell, not replacing it", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Change `renderCursorCell(cell, \"bar\")` to wrap `safeCell` in the bar cursor style instead of returning the `BAR_CURSOR_GLYPH`. For empty/end-of-line cursor cells, continue rendering a styled space. Rationale: the cursor cell remains exactly one visible cell wide and the character stays readable. Existing terminal cursor-shape hints still provide the real vertical-bar cursor in focused terminals."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_test_behavior_at_the_rendering_boundary", "label": "Test behavior at the rendering boundary", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 37", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Update tests to assert that `renderCursorCell(\"x\", \"bar\")` contains `x`, contains `CURSOR_BAR_START`, and does not contain/replace with `\u258c`. Add marker restyle coverage to ensure Pi-rendered cells keep their captured content after bar restyling. Rationale: the bug is isolated to the render boundary, and boundary tests avoid coupling to unrelated modal/editor behavior."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 47", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Bar fake cursor may look less like a vertical bar in non-focused snapshots \u2192 Mitigation: rely on terminal DECSCUSR in focused terminals and keep bold/visible styling as fallback. - ANSI nesting with existing cursor marker output could strip style from captured cells \u2192 Mitigation: test `restyleCursorMarker()` with captured styled and plain cells. - Wide-character cursor cells may have terminal-specific styling quirks \u2192 Mitigation: preserve current width accounting and add/keep width-safety cove"}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 53", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "No data migration or config migration required. Ship as a rendering fix. Rollback is reverting the small `src/render.ts` change plus tests. ## Open Questions"}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_open_questions", "label": "Open Questions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 57", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "None."}, {"id": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_ref_src_render_ts", "label": "render.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_decisions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 23", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_render_bar_by_styling_the_existing_cell_not_replacing_it", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_test_behavior_at_the_rendering_boundary", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 37", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_risks_trade_offs", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 47", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_migration_plan", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 53", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_open_questions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 57", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_document", "target": "2026_05_29_fix_bar_cursor_hides_character_design_ref_src_render_ts", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-29-fix-bar-cursor-hides-character/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", "weight": 1.0}], "hyperedges": []}